&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the full user lifecycle from sign-up through activation, conversion, retention, and expansion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and execute nurture programs tailored to where users are in their journey — onboarding sequences, re-engagement flows, and milestone-based triggers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and manage in-console messaging and product nudges in partnership with Product — surfacing the right prompt to the right user at the right moment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain user segmentation frameworks based on product usage, firmographics, and behavioural signals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive monetisation programs: identifying users with high conversion or expansion potential and delivering targeted interventions (upgrade prompts, usage-based triggers, tier nudges)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Product and Data teams to define the signals that indicate activation, health, and churn risk — and build automated responses to them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own lifecycle reporting: activation rates, conversion rates, expansion revenue influenced, and churn metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in lifecycle, CRM, or retention marketing, ideally at a SaaS or PLG company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of user journey mapping and funnel-based thinking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re highly data-driven, you can build a cohort, read a funnel, and turn behavioural signals into a clear hypothesis worth testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with marketing automation and lifecycle tooling (e.g. Customer.io, Braze, Iterable, or similar)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with in-product messaging tools (e.g. Intercom, Pendo, or similar) is a strong plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong collaboration skills, this role sits at the intersection of Marketing, Product, and Data&lt;/li&gt;
